[1]
Date: 3 Feb 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Newspaper Jornal do Brasil, Sat 3 Feb 2001 [translated & summarized
by Mod.JW]

Canada has banned importation of Brazilian beef on the grounds Brazil has
not provided the necessary information that it is BSE-free. The decision
was announced in the Canadian parliament by the Health Minister, Alan Rock.
It was stated Argentina, Uruguay, USA, Australia and New Zealand have
provided information showing themselves free of BSE, but Brazil has not.
In reply, the Brazilian secretary of Defesa Agropecuaria (livestock), Luiz
Carlos Oliveira, said Brazil has provided the information.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Since Brazilian beef is famous for being grass-fed, this seems like an
unnecessary bureaucratic wrangle. - Mod.JW]
