Date: 8 Feb 2001
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com
Source: Khaleej Times, 8 Feb 2001 [edited]
<http://www.khaleejtimes.com/middleeast.htm>

MUSCAT - Oman yesterday strongly refuted foreign Press reports it had
imported possibly contaminated blood or blood derivatives. A Health
Ministry spokesman said the Sultanate had stopped importing blood since
1991 and entirely depended on local donations to meets its requirements.
He added the ministry had the necessary laboratory facilities in place to
ensure the safety of blood and blood products. The spokesman said the
company from which the blood products were allegedly imported was not
registered with the ministry and "was never dealt with in this matter."
--
